        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 5:02PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Scottsburg, or near Clover, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Halifax...
Redoak...
Clover...
Scottsburg...
Mt Laurel...
Staunton River State Park...
and Dryburg.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
